
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Subject line: type(scope): description
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Types: Required noun describing commit type.
#
#    build - Changes build system or external dependencies.
#    chore - Changes external user won't see. (configs/internal task)
#       ci - Changes CI configuration files or scripts.
#     docs - Changes documentation only.
#     feat - A new feature.
#      fix - A bug fix.
#     perf - Change that improves performance.
# refactor - Change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature.
#   revert - Change that corrects a commit.
#    style - Changes don't affect meaning. (white-space, format, etc.)
#     test - Adds test or corrects existing test.
#
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Scope:       Optional noun describing relevant section of codebase.
#              Must be inside parenthesis if used.
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Description: Required short summary of the changes.
#              Must follow a colon after type or scope.
#              No ending punctuation.
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Body:        Optional longer description providing additional context.
#              Must begin one blank line after subject/title.
#              Free-form, may consist of newlines and paragraphs.
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Footer:      Optional git trailer.
#              Must begin one blank line after body paragraph.
#              Tokens must use '-' in place of white-space.
#              May contain spaces and newlines.
#
# References:  Links information/issues/commits/PRs.
#              Closed issues should be listed on separate line.
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: Must be indicated in title or footer.
#                  If title: Indicate using ! before colon. (!:)
#                            Must use body to describe.
#                  If footer: Must be uppercase text.
#                             Must have a colon and spaced description.
#                             Description should be lowercase.
#------------------------------------------------------------------------
